Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Reports say that the hijackers 
are demanding to be given fuel to fly to Rome, Italy. The 
reports add that the hijackers have released some of the crew to 
negotiate with authorities over their demands. Some news just 
in says the captain of the Saudi plane hijacked earlier this 
morning is being held hostage by one of the hijackers aboard the 
plane. 
  Many top Kenyan security men are reported to be at the 
airport. The reports add that British Petroleum-Shell officials 
were also seen at the airport. 

